5: Offset:
===============================================================================

   Har Partition ke andar har message ko ek unique Offset milta hai. Offset ek index ki tarah kaam karta hai jo message ki position batata hai.

   Maan lo Producer ne messages A, B, C, D aur E isi sequence me publish kiye hain.

   Suppose:
   Topic : "my-topic"
   It has only 1 partition

   Partition-0

   Offset 0 -> A
   Offset 1 -> B
   Offset 2 -> C
   Offset 3 -> D
   Offset 4 -> E

   Kyuki Topic me sirf ek hi Partition hai, isliye saare messages sequentially isi Partition me store honge.

   Consumer messages read karta hai partition se aur apna Offset commit karta rehta hai.

   Agar Consumer ne "C" successfully process kar liya aur Offset commit kar diya, to generally next read:

   Offset 3 -> D

   se start hogi.

   Kafka committed Offset ko store karke rakhta hai.

   Agar Consumer restart ho jaye, to Kafka last committed Offset check karta hai.

  Example:

  Last Committed Offset = 3

  To Consumer dubara start hote hi:

   Offset 3 -> D

  se reading continue karega.

  Consumer chahe to committed Offset ignore karke beginning se bhi read kar sakta hai.

  Example:

  "Mujhe saare messages dobara process karne hain."

  To Consumer:

  Offset 0 -> A

  se reading start kar sakta hai.

