11 : Rebalancing
===============================================================================

Rebalancing is the process in which Kafka redistributes partitions among consumers of a consumer group whenever the group membership changes,
such as when a new consumer joins, an existing consumer leaves, crashes, or becomes unavailable.

Maan lo:

Topic = Orders

Partitions:

P0
P1
P2

Maan lo 2 consumers (say C1 and C2) 'Orders' topic ko listen kar rahe hain aur dono same consumer group se belong karte hain, say 'order-group'.

order-group:

C1
C2

Kafka assignment:

P0 -> C1
P1 -> C2
P2 -> C1

Sab normal chal raha hai.

Rebalancing Kab Hota Hai?

Kafka ko jab lagta hai ki consumer group ki composition change ho gayi hai. Is case me 'order-group' ki composition change ho gayi.

Case 1: Naya Consumer Join Kare

Pehle:

C1
C2

Ab:

C1
C2
C3

Kafka sochega:

"Ab ek naya consumer aa gaya hai, kaam redistribute karna chahiye."

To reassignment karega.

Example:

P0 -> C1
P1 -> C2
P2 -> C3

Ye rebalancing hai.

Case 2: Consumer Crash Ho Jaye

Pehle:

P0 -> C1
P1 -> C2
P2 -> C3

Ab C3 crash ho gaya.

Kafka sochega:

"P2 ko ab kaun consume karega?"

Reassignment:

P0 -> C1
P1 -> C2
P2 -> C1

Ye bhi rebalancing hai.

Case 3: Consumer Restart Ho

Kafka ke liye restart bhi:

leave group
join group

jaisa hi hota hai.

Isliye rebalance trigger ho sakta hai.

