14 : ACKS Kya Hai?
===============================================================================

Maan lo Kafka cluster me multiple brokers hain:

Broker-1
Broker-2
Broker-3

Topic = Alphabet

Topic ke paas sirf 1 Partition hai:

Partition-0

Aur Replication Factor = 3 hai.

Matlab Partition-0 ki total 3 copies (replicas) hongi jo different brokers
par store hongi.

Partition Distribution:

Broker-1 -> Partition-0 (Leader)

Broker-2 -> Partition-0 (Follower)

Broker-3 -> Partition-0 (Follower)

Producer message bhejta hai: "A"

Jo Partition-0 ke Leader Replica (Broker-1) me store hota hai.

Uske baad Followers (In Broker-2 and Broker-3) Leader se data copy karenge.

i.e

Current State:

Leader Offset = 0 (Broker-1)

Follower-1 Offset = 0 (Broker-2)

Follower-2 Offset = 0 (Broker-3)


Question:

Leader producer ko kab bolega:

"Message Successfully Stored"

Iska answer ACKS configuration deta hai.

'acks' Producer-side setting hai.

Producer decide karta hai:

"Mujhe success kab maana hai?"

------------------------------------------------------------
Case 1: ACKS = 0
------------------------------------------------------------

Producer message publish karne ke baad bina kisi confirmation (from Leader Replica i.e. Partition-0 in Broker-1)
ka wait kiye aage badh jata hai i.e Producer wait hi nahi karta after publishing the message.

Advantage:
Fastest

Disadvantage:

Agar network issue hua:

Producer ----X----> Leader

To message gaya bhi ya nahi gaya,
producer ko pata nahi.

Data loss possible.

------------------------------------------------------------
Case 2: ACKS = 1
------------------------------------------------------------
Producer message publish karta hai ye message Partition-0 ke Leader Replica (i.e. Partition-0 in Broker-1)
ke paas jata hai.

Leader receive karta hai.

Leader disk par write karta hai.

Fir Producer ko ACK bhej deta hai.

Important:

Followers ne copy kiya ya nahi,
Producer ko koi farak nahi padta.

Bas Leader ne successfully write kar liya ho.

Problem

Current State:

Leader Offset = 0 (Broker-1)

Follower-1 Offset = 0 (Broker-2)

Follower-2 Offset = 0 (Broker-3)

Producer ne ek naya message bheja manlo "B"

Leader us message ko write kar deta hai:

Now 
Leader Offset = 1

Aur Producer ko ACK bhej deta hai.

Producer: SUCCESS

Lekin ussi second Leader crash ho gaya.

Followers tak Offset 1 wala message I.E "B"
abhi replicate hi nahi hua tha.

Current State:

Follower-1 Offset = 0 (Broker-2)

Follower-2 Offset = 0 (Broker-3)

ISR = {Follower-1, Follower-2}

Note:

ISR me hone ka matlab ye nahi hai ki replica har moment
Leader ke exact same Offset par hi ho.

ISR replicas thoda lag kar sakte hain,
lekin wo Leader ke sufficiently close aur synchronized maane jaate hain.

Ab Kafka ISR me se naya Leader elect karega.

Suppose:

Follower-1 (Partition-0 in Broker-2)

new Leader ban gaya.

Result:

Offset 101 wala message kisi replica tak pahucha hi nahi tha.

Isliye Offset 101 wala message lost ho gaya.

Data Loss.

------------------------------------------------------------
Case 3: ACKS = ALL
------------------------------------------------------------

Current State:

Leader Offset      = 0 (Broker-1)

Follower-1 Offset  = 0 (Broker-2)

Follower-2 Offset  = 0 (Broker-3)

ISR = {Leader, Follower-1, Follower-2}


Producer message publish karta hai.

Ye message Partition-0 ke Leader Replica
(i.e. Partition-0 on Broker-1)
ke paas jata hai.

Leader receive karta hai.

Leader disk par message write karta hai.

Ab Leader wait karega.

Jab tak ye message sabhi ISR replicas tak
replicate nahi ho jata.

Uske baad hi Producer ko ACK bheja jayega.

Example:

Producer ne ek naya message bheja:

"B"


Leader us message ko write kar deta hai.

Updated State:

Leader Offset = 1


Ab Leader (Partition-0 on Broker-1)
wait karega jab tak baaki ISR replicas
(Partition-0 on Broker-2 and Broker-3)
bhi is message ko write na kar lein.

Final State:

Leader Offset      = 1

Follower-1 Offset  = 1

Follower-2 Offset  = 1


Ab Kafka Producer ko ACK bhej dega.

------------------------------------------
## Kya ACKS = ALL Matlab Sab Replicas?
------------------------------------------

Nahi.

Kafka bolta hai:

ALL ISR REPLICAS

Not:

ALL REPLICAS

Difference samjho.

Example:

Assume ek Topic hai jisme:

Partitions         = 1

Replication Factor = 3

Matlab Partition-0 ki total 3 copies hongi, jo different Brokers par stored hongi.

In 3 replicas me:

* 1 Leader Replica hoga
* 2 Follower Replicas hongi

Replicas:

Leader
Follower-1
Follower-2

Maan lo currently dono followers completely synced hain with Leader Partition.

Current State:

Leader      Offset = 10
Follower-1  Offset = 10
Follower-2  Offset = 10

Current ISR:

{Leader, Follower-1, Follower-2}

Ab Producer aur bhi bahut saare messages bhejta hai.

Saare messages Leader tak pahunch jaate hain aur Follower-1 tak bhi successfully replicate ho jaate hain.

Lekin kisi reason se Follower-2 un messages ko receive nahi kar pata aur bahut piche reh jaata hai.

Updated State:

Leader      Offset = 100
Follower-1  Offset = 100
Follower-2  Offset = 40

Ab Follower-2 Leader se kaafi piche hai.

Kafka ise Out Of Sync maanega aur ISR se remove kar dega.

Updated ISR:

{Leader, Follower-1}

Ab Producer:

acks = all

use kar raha hai.

Question:

Kya Leader Follower-2 ke sync hone ka bhi wait karega?

Answer:

No.

Leader sirf ISR members ke sync hone ka wait karega.

Is case me:

ISR = {Leader, Follower-1}

To Leader sirf Follower-1 ke sync hone ka wait karega.

Follower-2 ke liye wait nahi karega.

Kyun?

Kyuki Follower-2 ISR ka member hi nahi hai.

Important:

acks=all ka matlab:

"Wait for all ISR replicas"

NOT

"Wait for every replica present in the cluster"

--------------------------
min.insync.replicas
--------------------------

Yahi sabse important production setting hai.

Example:

Assume ek Topic hai jisme:

Partitions         = 1
Replication Factor = 3

Matlab Partition-0 ki total 3 copies hongi, jo different Brokers par stored hongi.

In 3 replicas me:

* 1 Leader Replica hoga
* 2 Follower Replicas hongi

Replicas:

Leader
Follower-1
Follower-2

Maan lo currently dono followers completely synced hain with Leader.

Current State:

Leader      Offset = 10
Follower-1  Offset = 10
Follower-2  Offset = 10

Current ISR:

{Leader, Follower-1, Follower-2}

Ab Producer:

acks=all

use kar raha hai.

Question:

"Producer ko success kab milega?"

Kafka bolega:

Jab ISR ke saare replicas me message aa jaye.



